abstract: West Indies beats Zimbabwe in the Cricket World Cup, as Chris Gayle scores a cup innings record of 215.
lead_paragraph: Chris Gayle scored a record Cricket World Cup innings of 215 to lead West Indies to a 73-run win over Zimbabwe. Gayle also had a record-equaling 16 sixes in his innings.

headline.main: Record Set in World Cup Victory for West Indies
headline.print_headline: Record Set in Victory for West Indies
